HEADWORD: Catastasis
<hw>Ca*tas"ta*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to set; <grk>kata`</grk> down + <?/ to place.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>That part of a speech, usually the
exordium, in which the orator sets forth the subject matter to be
discussed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The state, or condition of
anything; constitution; habit of body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Catasterism</ent>⟦br⟧
